      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good race but hard to go past BELVEDERE ROCK (3) who is ready to win after two runs in. Missed the frame latest but got a long way back and stormed home in an eye-catching run. Loves the mile and won only try third-up. Looks ready. CANDLELIGHT SHERIF (4) did a good job last time, finishing in the money when third over 1600m at this track. Has a tricky draw to overcome but looks a genuine threat. IRONCLAD BOY (6) finished 3 lengths away in fourth last time out over 1400m at this track after being prominent at the corner a week ago. Tackles a longer journey this time. Low draw and will take catching. ODIN OMEN (7) was allowed to drift back from an outside draw but found the line strongly to finish fourth, beaten 5 lengths, over 1600m here last time. Can feature in the finish. DAIYAMONDO (5) has been a long time out of the winners list but looks close and can give a sight.",
